tatic\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5752435\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104btl1705400316529.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/btl1705400316529.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/btl1705400316529.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zoq1665702624324\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                 \n Script the Component Behavior\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the Write Script worksheet to script the component's functionality, include the actions it executes, the way it responds to events, the validation it performs when data is loaded or stored, and so on.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"zoq1665702624324__context_w1829ab1b5b1_w1830ab1b5_w1831ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"zoq1665702624324__topic_d12092e1_d12093e1_d12094e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zoq1665702624324__p_d12095e1_d12096e1_d12097e1\">Uniface provides a great deal of default behavior, especially for data retrieval and storage, locking, and transaction control. You can enhance or override Uniface's default behavior and behavior inherited from the model.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zoq1665702624324__li_d5591e1_d5592e1_d5593e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Write Script</span> tab to switch to the Write Script worksheet.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zoq1665702624324__li_d5594e1_d5595e1_d5596e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd stepresult\" id=\"zoq1665702624324__p_d12098e1_d12099e1_d12100e1\">In the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Structure</span> pane, select the component, entity, or field for which you want to script behavior.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zoq1665702624324__p_d12101e1_d12102e1_d12103e1\">The Code Editor shows the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Declarations</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Script</span> code containers for the object. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"caq1665702624398.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/caq1665702624398.html\" title=\"Code containers are properties of components, application shells, entities and fields that hold the ProcScript and JavaScript code used to define application behavior for the specific object.\">Code Containers</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"zoq1665702624324__note_w1832ab1b5b3b3b3b3b1_w1833ab1b5b3b3b3b3_w1834ab1b5b3b3b3_w1835ab1b5b3b3_w1836ab1b5b3_w1837ab1b5_w1838ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> If modeled entities and fields already contain code, this is inherited, but it is not displayed in the component. Writing script in a trigger with inherited code overrides the modeled code.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zoq1665702624324__li_d5597e1_d5598e1_d5599e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Declare a script module by typing the declaration or inserting a code snippet in its Script container.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger <var class=\"keyword varname\">ValidTriggerName</var><var class=\"keyword varname\">Your Code Here</var>\nend\noperation <var class=\"keyword varname\">YourOperationName</var><var class=\"keyword varname\">Your Code Here</var>\nend</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"zoq1665702624324__pre_ohb_c11_vcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger <var class=\"keyword varname\">ValidTriggerName</var><var class=\"keyword varname\">Your Code Here</var>\nend\noperation <var class=\"keyword varname\">YourOperationName</var><var class=\"keyword varname\">Your Code Here</var>\nend</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zoq1665702624324__p_d12107e1_d12108e1_d12109e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gtm1665702624482.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gtm1665702624482.html\" title=\"A script module is a named collection of ProcScript belonging to a development object. Script modules are analogous to events and methods in other programming languages.\">Script Modules</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zoq1665702624324__p_d12110e1_d12111e1_d12112e1\">To use a code snippet as a template:</p>\n</div>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"zoq1665702624324__li_d5600e1_d5601e1_d5602e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Resource Browser, select a Snippet Library.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"zoq1665702624324__li_d5603e1_d5604e1_d5605e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Select the snippet for the desired trigger, right-click and select <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Insert</span>.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"zoq1665702624324__li_d5606e1_d5607e1_d5608e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Program the desired behavior using ProcScript. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kvf1665702667063.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kvf1665702667063.html\" title=\"Uniface enables you to script application behavior using ProcScript, Uniface's own scripting language, and JavaScript, the most widely-used scripting language for web applications.\">Scripting Application Behavior</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jcx1707814817129.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jcx1707814817129.html\" title=\"ProcScript provides high-level statements, functions, expressions, and operators that enable you to efficiently manipulate data and script application behavior. It is a powerful language that condenses complex processing into single commands.\">ProcScript Syntax</a>.\n                    </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"zoq1665702624324__note_w1839ab1b5b3b7b3b1_w1840ab1b5b3b7b3_w1841ab1b5b3b7_w1842ab1b5b3_w1843ab1b5_w1844ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> For dynamic server pages, you can also use JavaScript to code\n                  client-side behavior. Uniface provides a JavaScript API so that you address\n                  Uniface objects from JavaScript. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"owl1665702532596.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/owl1665702532596.html\" title=\"The Uniface JavaScript API is a collection of object-oriented programming interfaces that can be used in dynamic server pages (DSPs) to manipulate Uniface data objects in the browser, without round-trip processing to the server.\">APIs: DSP Client-Side JavaScript</a>. </div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5752435\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5752435\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Script the Component Behavior Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Script the Component Behavior Use the Write Script worksheet to script the component's functionality, include the actions it executes, the way it responds to events, the validation it performs when data is loaded or stored, and so on. Uniface provides a great deal of default behavior, especially for data retrieval and storage, locking, and transaction control. You can enhance or override Uniface's default behavior and behavior inherited from the model. Click the Write Script tab to switch to the Write Script worksheet. In the Structure pane, select the component, entity, or field for which you want to script behavior. The Code Editor shows the Declarations and Script code containers for the object. For more information, see Code Containers . Note: If modeled entities and fields already contain code, this is inherited, but it is not displayed in the component. Writing script in a trigger with inherited code overrides the modeled code. Declare a script module by typing the declaration or inserting a code snippet in its Script container. trigger ValidTriggerName Your Code Here end operation YourOperationName Your Code Here end Copy trigger ValidTriggerName Your Code Here end operation YourOperationName Your Code Here end Copy For more information, see Script Modules . To use a code snippet as a template: In the Resource Browser, select a Snippet Library. Select the snippet for the desired trigger, right-click and select Insert . Program the desired behavior using ProcScript. For more information, see Scripting Application Behavior and ProcScript Syntax . Note: For dynamic server pages, you can also use JavaScript to code client-side behavior. Uniface provides a JavaScript API so that you address Uniface objects from JavaScript. For more information, see APIs: DSP Client-Side JavaScript . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}